A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 10 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to obstruction of public administration and related offenses, so as to provide for a
3 mandatory minimum sentence for those convicted of doing violence in the obstruction or
4 hindering of law enforcement officers; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
5 laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 2 of Chapter 10 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 obstruction of public administration and related offenses, is amended by revising Code
10 Section 16-10-24, relating to obstructing or hindering law enforcement officers, as follows:
11 "16-10-24.
12 (a) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (b) of this Code section, a person who
13 knowingly and willfully obstructs or hinders any law enforcement officer, prison guard,
14 jailer, correctional officer, community supervision officer, county or Department of
15 Juvenile Justice juvenile probation officer, probation officer serving pursuant to Article 6
