16 of Chapter 8 of Title 42, or game warden in the lawful discharge of his or her official duties
17 shall be guilty of a misdemeanor.
18 (b)(1) Whoever knowingly and willfully resists, obstructs, or opposes any law
19 enforcement officer, prison guard, jailer, correctional officer, community supervision
20 officer, county or Department of Juvenile Justice juvenile probation officer, probation
21 officer serving pursuant to Article 6 of Chapter 8 of Title 42, or game warden in the
22 lawful discharge of his or her official duties by offering or doing violence to the person
23 of such officer or legally authorized person shall be guilty of a felony and shall, upon a
24 first conviction thereof, be punished by imprisonment for not less than one year nor more
25 than five years. Upon a second conviction for a violation of this subsection, such person
26 shall be punished by imprisonment for not less than two years nor more than ten years.
27 Upon a third or subsequent conviction for a violation of this subsection, such person shall
28 be punished by imprisonment for not less than three years nor more than 15 years.
29 (2) Whoever knowingly and willfully resists, obstructs, or opposes any law enforcement
30 officer, prison guard, jailer, correctional officer, community supervision officer, county
31 or Department of Juvenile Justice juvenile probation officer, probation officer serving
32 pursuant to Article 6 of Chapter 8 of Title 42, or game warden in the lawful discharge of
33 his or her official duties by doing violence to the person of such officer or legally
34 authorized person shall be guilty of a felony and shall, upon conviction thereof, be
35 punished by imprisonment for not less than ten years nor more than 20 years.
36 (c) Whoever knowingly and willfully resists, obstructs, or opposes any law enforcement
37 officer, prison guard, jailer, correctional officer, community supervision officer, county or
38 Department of Juvenile Justice juvenile probation officer, probation officer serving
39 pursuant to Article 6 of Chapter 8 of Title 42, or game warden in the lawful discharge of
40 his or her official duties by knowingly and willfully throwing, projecting, or expelling
41 human or animal blood, urine, feces, vomitus, or seminal fluid on or at such individual
